A new Guinness World Record has been broken by a team of United Arab Emirates chefs who came together to bake 2,209 pies and arranging them into a line. The record attempt, organised by the Emirates Culinary Guild and USA Pears, featured the chefs baking pear pies at the Madinat Jumeirah resort in Dubai thereby breaking the previous record of 1,608 pies, which was done in Australia in 2016. The record breaking chefs are Emirates Flight Catering, Caesars Bluewaters Dubai, Jumeirah Creekside, Radisson Blu Hotel DDC, Madinat Jumeirah, Le Meridien Airport, JW Marriott Marquis Hotel Dubai, Crown Plaza Shaikh Zayed Road, Waldorf Astoria DIFC, DoubleTree by Hilton JBR, Bakemart, Sarood Hospitality and students from International Center for Culinary Arts Dubai. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The pies were donated to food access charity Sahem for the less privileged.